<function>

access:   public

name: uri

param: mixed, $value

param: string|array, $schemes, NULL

param: bool, $blank, false

return: bool

</function>

Validate a value as a URI per RFC2396.

* Parameters:

 * mixed //$value//: The value to validate.

 * string|array //$schemes//: Allowed schemes for the URI; e.g., http, https, ftp.  If null, all schemes are allowed.

 * bool //$blank//: Allow blank values to be valid.

* Returns bool: True if the value is a URI and is one of the allowed schemes, false if not.

The value must match a generic URI format; e.g.,
``http://example.com``, ``mms://example.org``, and so on.